<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>How does skill play into this test?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Mizari">Mizari</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:21 p.m. 9/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> How does skill play into this test?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=408" TARGET=_self>I've tested it including L18 Pal vs L16 Ranger</A> (TheBlack[BCK])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Guess I'm just wondering (hoping) if there were any other possible causes to that discrepancy.

<P>How did combat skill levels compare (weapons, dodging, offense/defense etc.)? at 2 xp levels I'm assuming there could be as much as a 10-15 skill level discrepancy between the two. (2 xp levels is a lot of potential skill)
<P>Is there a possibility that some other skill could have swayed the results? At 18th lvl the pally could have some decent parrying skill built up that the ranger couldn't get yet.
<P>Is the problem really just level centric... or is it skill centric based on the skill cap per level. I had assumed skills still had more direct effect on your overall effectiveness than anything (quite possibly I'm badly mistaken it sounds)
<P>&gt; I have test results for a L18 Paladin vs L16 Ranger. The Ranger
<BR>&gt; had equal or better ATK and DAM numbers due to buffing, and a
<BR>&gt; higher AC. The Ranger also had dual attack and equal or better
<BR>&gt; weapons than the Paladin. The Paladin beat the crap out of the
<BR>&gt; Ranger and forced the Ranger to zone near death and out of mana
<BR>&gt; while the Paladin was at full mana and not significantly hurt.
<BR>&gt; The Paladin did not even use Lay Hands and the Ranger used good
<BR>&gt; tactics (superior to the Paladin). The main difference was the
<BR>&gt; levels.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
